@node ARMOR "Armor Thrull"

@{b}Armor Thrull@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Summon Thrull (1/3)
Cost    = 2B
Artist  = Jeff A. Menges / Pete Venters / Ron Spencer / Scott Kirschner

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are FOUR different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): <T>: Sacrifice Armor Thrull to put a +1/+2 counter on a target
          creature.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Except for a bare spot at the base of their skulls, Armor
              Thrulls bear interlocking plates and spikes with the
              strength of steel. Their design is almost artistic."
              ---Endrek Sahr, 'Thrulls'@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"The worst thing about being a mercenary for the Ebon
              Hand is having to wear a dead Thrull."
              ---Ivra Jursdotter@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"They gave their lives to strengthen the Order's armies,
              until they declined this honor in favor of joining the
              Thrull Rebellion."
              ---Jherana Rure, Counter-Insurgency Commander@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}Occasionally, an ally balked at wearing a dead Thrull as
             armor. The priests' whips, however, were usually enough
             to encourage a more practical outlook.@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node BASAL "Basal Thrull"

@{b}Basal Thrull@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Summon Thrull (1/2)
Cost    = BB
Artist  = Christopher Rush / Kaja Foglio / Phil Foglio / Richard Kane Ferguson

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are FOUR different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): <T>: Sacrifice Basal Thrull to add <BB> to your mana pool.
          Play this ability as an interrupt.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Above all, a well crafted Thrull should be hideous
              - blasted of countenance and twisted of limb - to
              inspire fear and revulsion."
              ---Endrek Sahr, Master Breeder@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}Initially bred for sacrifice, the Thrulls eventually turned
             on their masters, the Order of the Ebon Hand, with gruesome
             results.
             @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. II

Flavor Text: @{i}"Although my later designs were much more sophisticated,
              Basal Thrulls were no less a success."
              ---Endrek Sahr, 'Thrulls'@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"To create the first Thrulls, I only introduced alchemic
              elements into the Order's necromancy; Tourach's principles
              remained unchanged."
              ---Endrek Sahr, Master Breeder@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_B.guide/BASAL}

@endnode
@node BREED "Breeding Pit"

@{b}Breeding Pit@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(U3) / 5E(U)
Type    = Enchantment
Cost    = 3B
Artist  = Anson Maddocks (FE) / Adrian Smith (5E)

Text(5E): During your upkeep, pay <BB> or bury Breeding Pit. At the end
          of your turn, put a Thrull token into play. Treat this token
          as a 0/1 black creature.

Text(FE): During your upkeep, pay <BB> or bury Breeding Pit. At the end of
          your turn, put a Thrull token into play. Treat this token as a
          0/1 black creature.

Flavor Text: @{i}The Thrulls bred at a terrifying pace. In the end, they
             overwhelmed the Order of the Ebon Hand.@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_B.guide/BREED}

@endnode
@node DEREL "Derelor"

@{b}Derelor@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(U1) / 5E(R)
Type    = Summon Thrull (4/4)
Cost    = 3B
Artist  = Anson Maddocks

Text(5E): Your black spells cost an additional <B> to play.

Text(FE): Your black spells cost an additional <B> to cast.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Strength it has, but at the cost of a continuous supply
              of energy. Such failure can bear only one result."
              ---From the execution order for Endrek Sahr, Master Breeder@{ui}

 @{b}NO RULINGS@{ub}

@endnode
@node EBONP "Ebon Praetor"

@{b}Ebon Praetor@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(U1)
Type    = Summon Avatar (5/5)
Cost    = 4BB
Artist  = Randy Asplund-Faith

Text(FE): Trample, first strike
          During your upkeep, put a -2/-2 counter on Ebon Praetor. You may
          sacrifice a creature during your upkeep to remove a -2/-2 counter
          from Ebon Praetor. If the creature sacrificed was a Thrull, also
          put a +1/+0 counter on Ebon Praetor. Only one creature may be
          sacrificed in this manner each turn.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_E.guide/EBPRA}

@endnode
@node HYMNT "Hymn to Tourach"

@{b}Hymn to Tourach@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1/C1)
Type    = Sorcery
Cost    = BB
Artist  = Liz Danforth / Quinton Hoover / Scott Kirschner / Susan van Camp

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are FOUR different artworks for this card.

Text(FE): Target player discards two cards at random from his or her hand.
          If target player does not have enough cards, his or her entire
          hand is discarded.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Tourach's power was such that his followers
              deified him after his death."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. II

Flavor Text: @{i}Knowing the Hymn's power, the followers of Leitbur
             carefully guarded their pillaged transcriptions.@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}Members of the Order often played the Hymn on instruments
             made from their victims' bones.@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"The eerie, wailing Hymn caused insanity even in
              hardened warriors."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. II

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_H.guide/HYMTT}

@endnode
@node INITI "Initiates of the Ebon Hand"

@{b}Initiates of the Ebon Hand@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1) / 5E(C)
Type    = Summon Clerics (1/1)
Cost    = B
Artist  = Heather Hudson (FE/5E) / Kaja Foglio (FE) / Liz Danforth (FE)

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(5E): <1>: Add <B> to your mana pool. If <4> or more is spent in this
          way during one turn, bury Initiates of the Ebon Hand at end of
          turn. Play this ability as a mana source.

Text(FE): <1>: Add <B> to your mana pool.
          Play this ability as an interrupt. If more than <3> is spent in
          this way during one turn, bury Initiates of the Ebon Hand at end
          of turn.

Flavor Text: @{i}"We are no longer Nature's children, but her masters..."
              ---Oath of the Ebon Hand@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}"Many Initiates sacrificed a hand to become full
              members of the Order."
              @{ui}---Sarpadian Empires, vol. II

Flavor Text: @{i}Ebon leaders soon realized that non-human races often
             had special talents that could be exploited.@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_I.guide/INITI}

@endnode
@node MINDS "Mindstab Thrull"

@{b}Mindstab Thrull@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1) / 5E(C)
Type    = Summon Thrull (2/2)
Cost    = 1BB
Artist  = Heather Hudson (FE) / Richard Kane Ferguson (FE)
          Mark Tedin (FE/5E)

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(5E): Sacrifice Mindstab Thrull: Defending player chooses and
          discards three cards. Use this ability only if Mindstab
          Thrull is attacking and unblocked.

Text(FE): If Mindstab Thrull attacks and is not blocked, you may sacrifice
          it to force the player it attacked to discard three cards. If
          you do so, it deals no damage during combat this turn. If that
          player does not have enough cards, his or her entire hand is
          discarded.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_M.guide/MINDS}

@endnode
@node NECRI "Necrite"

@{b}Necrite@{ub}

Color   = Black
Rarity  = FE(C1/C1/C1) / 5E(C)
Type    = Summon Thrull (2/2)
Cost    = 1BB
Artist  = Christopher Rush (FE) / Drew Tucker (FE)
          Ron Spencer (FE/5E)

@{b}NOTE@{ub}: There are THREE different artworks for this card.

Text(5E): Sacrifice Necrite: Bury target creature defending player
          controls. Use this ability only if Necrite is attacking
          and unblocked.

Text(FE): If Necrite attacks and is not blocked, you may sacrifice it to
          bury a target creature controlled by the player Necrite attacked
          this turn. If you do so, Necrite deals no damage during combat
          this turn.

Flavor Text: @{i}"Ever see a wall drop dead of fright, kid?
              It ain't pretty."
              ---Cpl. Dobbs@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}Was it the sight, smell, or aura of the Necrite
             that killed so effectively?@{ui}

Flavor Text: @{i}Necrites killed Jherana Rure, ending
             the counter-insurgency.@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_N.guide/NECRI}

@endnode
